 205:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      ==================================
 206:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      [..]
 207:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        Below the list of most used macros in I2C HAL driver.
 208:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c **** 
 209:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****       (+) @ref __HAL_I2C_ENABLE:     Enable the I2C peripheral
 210:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****       (+) @ref __HAL_I2C_DISABLE:    Disable the I2C peripheral
 211:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****       (+) @ref __HAL_I2C_GET_FLAG:   Checks whether the specified I2C flag is set or not
 212:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****       (+) @ref __HAL_I2C_CLEAR_FLAG: Clear the specified I2C pending flag
 213:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****       (+) @ref __HAL_I2C_ENABLE_IT:  Enable the specified I2C interrupt
 214:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****       (+) @ref __HAL_I2C_DISABLE_IT: Disable the specified I2C interrupt
 215:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c **** 
 216:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      *** Callback registration ***
 217:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      =============================================
 218:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 219:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      The compilation flag USE_HAL_I2C_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 220:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 221:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Use Functions @ref HAL_I2C_RegisterCallback() or @ref HAL_I2C_RegisterAddrCallback()
 222:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      to register an interrupt callback.
 223:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 224:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Function @ref HAL_I2C_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
 225:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MasterTxCpltCallback : callback for Master transmission end of transfer.
 226:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MasterRxCpltCallback : callback for Master reception end of transfer.
 227:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) SlaveTxCpltCallback  : callback for Slave transmission end of transfer.
 228:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) SlaveRxCpltCallback  : callback for Slave reception end of transfer.
 229:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) ListenCpltCallback   : callback for end of listen mode.
 230:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MemTxCpltCallback    : callback for Memory transmission end of transfer.
 231:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MemRxCpltCallback    : callback for Memory reception end of transfer.
 232:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) ErrorCallback        : callback for error detection.
 233:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) AbortCpltCallback    : callback for abort completion process.
 234:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MspInitCallback      : callback for Msp Init.
 235:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MspDeInitCallback    : callback for Msp DeInit.
 236:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 237:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      and a pointer to the user callback function.
 238:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 239:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      For specific callback AddrCallback use dedicated register callbacks : @ref HAL_I2C_RegisterAdd
 240:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 241:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Use function @ref HAL_I2C_UnRegisterCallback to reset a callback to the default
 242:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      weak function.
 243:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      @ref HAL_I2C_UnRegisterCallback takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 244:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      and the Callback ID.
 245:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 246:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MasterTxCpltCallback : callback for Master transmission end of transfer.
 247:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MasterRxCpltCallback : callback for Master reception end of transfer.
 248:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) SlaveTxCpltCallback  : callback for Slave transmission end of transfer.
 249:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) SlaveRxCpltCallback  : callback for Slave reception end of transfer.
 250:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) ListenCpltCallback   : callback for end of listen mode.
 251:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MemTxCpltCallback    : callback for Memory transmission end of transfer.
 252:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MemRxCpltCallback    : callback for Memory reception end of transfer.
 253:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) ErrorCallback        : callback for error detection.
 254:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) AbortCpltCallback    : callback for abort completion process.
 255:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MspInitCallback      : callback for Msp Init.
 256:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MspDeInitCallback    : callback for Msp DeInit.
 257:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 258:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      For callback AddrCallback use dedicated register callbacks : @ref HAL_I2C_UnRegisterAddrCallba
ARM GAS  C:\Users\LENOVO\AppData\Local\Temp\ccOgQZgo.s 			page 6


 259:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 260:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      By default, after the @ref HAL_I2C_Init() and when the state is @ref HAL_I2C_STATE_RESET
 261:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 262:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      examples @ref HAL_I2C_MasterTxCpltCallback(), @ref HAL_I2C_MasterRxCpltCallback().
 263:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are
 264:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      reset to the legacy weak functions in the @ref HAL_I2C_Init()/ @ref HAL_I2C_DeInit() only when
 265:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 266:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      If MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the @ref HAL_I2C_Init()/ @ref HAL_I2C_DeInit()
 267:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand) whatever the state.
 268:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 269:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in @ref HAL_I2C_STATE_READY state only.
 270:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit functions that can be registered/unregistered
 271:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      in @ref HAL_I2C_STATE_READY or @ref HAL_I2C_STATE_RESET state,
 272:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 273:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Then, the user first registers the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 274:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      using @ref HAL_I2C_RegisterCallback() before calling @ref HAL_I2C_DeInit()
 275:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      or @ref HAL_I2C_Init() function.
 276:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 277:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      When the compilation flag USE_HAL_I2C_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 278:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all callbacks
 279:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_i2c.c ****      are set to the corresponding weak functions.
